# crontab.example -- monitoruloficial.ro scraper
#
# HOW TO INSTALL (safe -- doesn't overwrite existing entries):
#   crontab -e          <- opens your existing crontab in $EDITOR
#   append the lines below, save and quit
#
# Variable naming:
#   Variables in crontab are GLOBAL to the whole file -- a bare PYTHON= or
#   REPO= would collide with other projects. Use MO_* prefixes to be safe.
#
# Virtual environment:
#   Point MO_PYTHON directly at the venv binary -- do NOT use `source activate`.
#   `source` only works in interactive shells; cron runs /bin/sh with no profile.
#   Find the path on VPS while venv is active:  which python

MO_REPO=/home/pax/g2-dev/monitoruloficial
MO_PYTHON=/home/pax/g2-dev/monitorulpreturilor/venv/bin/python

# Twice-daily pipeline: index + ephemeral PDFs (Parts III-VII)
# Runs at 10:00 and 22:00, Mon-Fri (gazette is only published on weekdays).
# main.py orchestrates: get_index.py -> fetch_p3+.py
# Scripts log to $MO_REPO/data/logs/mof.log; cron stdout goes to /dev/null.

0 10,22 * * 1-5  $MO_PYTHON $MO_REPO/main.py >> /dev/null 2>&1

# Persistent PDFs (Parts I, II, PIM, V)
# Run once daily; only downloads what's missing (idempotent).
# On first run after VPS setup, add -start 2011-01-01 to skip empty pre-2011 rows.

30 10   * * 1-5  $MO_PYTHON $MO_REPO/fetch_pdfs.py >> /dev/null 2>&1

# Merge per-page PDFs into single documents
# Run after fetch_p3+.py has finished (offset by ~15 min to be safe).

15 10,22 * * 1-5  $MO_PYTHON $MO_REPO/concat_pages.py >> /dev/null 2>&1

# Optional: convert PDFs -> Markdown
# CPU-intensive; run once daily at a quiet time.
# Remove or comment out if text extraction isn't needed yet.

0 23    * * 1-5  $MO_PYTHON $MO_REPO/convert.py >> /dev/null 2>&1

# Notes:
#   Monitor runs:   $MO_PYTHON $MO_REPO/stats.py
#   Tail logs:      tail -f $MO_REPO/data/logs/mof.log
#   Check cron:     sudo journalctl -u cron   (systemd)
#                   /var/mail/$USER            (legacy)
